[1
Date: 21 Feb 2001
From: The Pig Disease Information Centre <pdic@btinternet.com> [edited
Source: BBC news 21 Feb 2001 6:30 GMT

All UK exports of livestock, meat products and milk have been banned. The
foot and mouth disease (FMD) virus strain is said to resemble strains from
Japan and Africa.
Further news will be posted at:
<http://www.pighealth.com>
