[2
Date: 21 Feb 2001
From: Pig Disease Information Centre <pdic@btinternet.com>
Source: UK Ministry of Agriculture, Fisheries and Food, 21 Feb 2001
<http://www.maff.gov.uk/>

Export Restrictions for Live Animals and Animal Products
------------------------------------------
This afternoon the European Commission brought into force a Decision which
restricts exports of live animals and animal products from the United
Kingdom to other Member States of the European Union.
At 11:00 tonight a UK statutory instrument will come into force which will
give effect to the Commission Decision. The full text of the UK statutory
instrument will be placed on this website tomorrow morning. But for now, we
present below a summary of the main points of the Commission Decision.
The Decision prohibits exports to other Member States of: live animals of
the porcine, bovine, ovine and caprine species, and other biungulates;
fresh meat of the porcine, bovine, ovine and caprine species, and other
biungulates, obtained on or after 1 Feb 2001; meat products of animals of
the porcine, bovine, ovine and caprine species, and other biungulates,
unless they meet certain specified conditions; milk, unless it has been
subjected to certain specified treatments; milk products produced on or
after 1 Feb 2001, unless it has been subjected to certain treatments;
semen, ova and embryos of the porcine, bovine, ovine and caprine species,
and other biungulates, with the exception of frozen bovine semen and
embryos produced before 1 Feb 2001; hides and skins of the porcine, bovine,
ovine and caprine species, and other biungulates, unless they were produced
before 1 Feb 2001, or conform to certain specified requirements; any other
animal products of the porcine, bovine, ovine and caprine species, and
other biungulates, unless they have been subjected to certain specified
heat treatments (excluding unprocessed sheep wool and ruminant hair which
is securely enclosed in packaging and dry).
Where the above refers to 'specified conditions' or some similar term, the
Commission Decision sets out additional certification requirements in order
for products to be traded. Full details of these conditions and the
certification requirements will be provided tomorrow.
Further news and developments will be posted at:
<http://www.pighealth.com>
--
The Pig Disease Information Centre
<pdic@ @btinternet.com>
