[Type O FMDv is found worldwide. It is clear from the latest report that
the subtype is known, and is a common one; more information is still needed.
It is unclear whether vesiculated animals have been found at all 4 sites.
Initially the sick animals were at the abattoir only and the 2 source herds
were unaffected. If that stands up, the animals would have been infected en
route, perhaps by sharing a contaminated, inadequately cleaned cattle truck.
If the former (i.e. dirty truck/lorry), there are other sick herds awaiting
discovery.
For those uninformed on this viral infection, pigs show fewer symptoms but
put out greater than 4 log units more virus than cattle. Therefore there
could be secondary cattle outbreaks. - Mods.MHJ/TG
